Nigerian singer, Iyanya Mbuk, has revealed why he pushed a fan off the stage during a concert in Awka, Anambra State. This comes after he was bashed online over a video of him pushing a fan off the stage. Iyanya took to his Twitter handle on Sunday to explain why he pushed the fan. ALSO READ: Four policemen remanded over extra-judiciary killing of youth in Ajah He claimed that the fan slapped him in the face with money and that, despite the fan’s hands, he continued. “The guy kept slapping my face with the money and I tried to hold his hand and he continued. First no matter how much you are spraying, don’t slap someone with it, that’s disrespectful,” he said. 